Character: 8\
Overall, characterization was allright. I did have a hard time warming up to Saki, the lead girl, because I found her attitude towards Satoru at the beginning of the series too antagonistic and her aggressiveness was never explained... especially since he was from the beginning a pretty nice child who only argued when Saki reacted badly... i.e all the time.\
I also had a hard time warming up to Shun. He was a bit too perfect to be true. All the kids in the group had their qualities and faults but Shun was too mature, too kind even as a young child. That made him completely unrealistic and difficult to relate to in my book though..\
