While I loved Satoru from the start, the same cannot be said about the other characters. It just felt like Satoru and Saki were the most balanced out of the lot: Mamoru is the crybaby, Shun the smart, brilliant and kind one and Maria, the protector of the weak. \
And while Satoru and Saki evolve as they grow up, I just didn't get the same feeling for the 3 others. If I had something to reproach that would be that.\
There's also a bunch of secondary characters that I would love to talk about but that would be useless. Watch the anime instead.\
\
Enjoyment: 7\
\
Objectively, I thought this series was amazing but I can't say that I fully enjoyed it. Enjoying would mean that I had experienced pleasure watching this when I generally felt ill at ease and disturbed.\
Il at ease concerning their society and the conception of a Utopia - a bonobo like society for instance. Do I think it's better to make love not war. Yes certainly. But I don't really like the idea of humans behaving like animals  and making love when they feel stressed. This rejection is also felt by Saki early on but it just seems that as she grows up, she ends up accepting it.\
Love and Sex are totally separate just like with the bonobos.\
There are many ethical questions raised throughout the series... Some can be considered through the lens of this futuristic world... others such as the issue of Speciesism can be directly applied to our current Society.\
There is no good answer to the many questions raised in this series and the anime makes good on showing how the humans, whom Saki the narrator is part of, revels in their cruelty when challenged while being taught to be kind from birth. \
As I typed above, it's interesting how you can't help feeling disgusted by the cruelty displayed to the children who don't fit the mold and then are faced with the dire consequences of an act of kindness. \
\
Will I rewatch Shin Sekai Yori...\
I really don't know. It's different certainly. It's one of these rare instances when I am glad for having had the chance to watch something challenging that takes its viewers and their intelligence seriously but at the same time make me question myself on so many things I feel a bit overwhelmed and I just want to empty my head and watch something stupid.\
Go figure.\
What's for sure though, is that it gives food for thought and that I certainly won't forget it. \
