Shin Sekai Yori takes its viewers seriously. You're not bombarded with philosophical mumbo-jumbo and philosopher's quotes. It presents you with a Society which faced some challenges early on and resorted to its scientific knowledge to  build a world where violence doesn't exist at a certain price. While the intention was noble, one might wonder if this was the best course of action or if they even had the right to go down that road in the first place.\
I personally don't really know what to make of this but I'm sure that will give room to interesting discussions among anime lovers.\
